quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  36,28,"After his death, We did not send down any soldiers from the heaven against his people, nor did We have to do so"
  36,29,"It was no more than a single blast, and immediately they were extinguished"
  36,30,Alas for the humans! No messenger ever comes to them but they ridicule him
  36,31,Do they not see how many generations We destroyed before them who will never come back to them
  36,32,Yet all of them will be brought before Us
  36,33,"There is a sign for them in the dead land: We give it life and produce from it grain for them to eat"
  36,34,"And We have made therein gardens of palm trees and grapevines, and caused springs to gush forth"
  36,35,so that they may eat of its fruit that was not made by their hands. Will they not then give thanks
  36,36,"Glory be to the One Who created all types of things that the earth produces, and of themselves, and of things that they have no knowledge about"
  36,37,"There is another sign for them in the night: We strip from it the daylight, and they are left in darkness"
  36,38,"The sun is running to its determined course. That is the design of the All-Mighty, All-Knowing"
  36,39,"As for the moon, We have determined phases for it, until it becomes like an old palm stalk"
  36,40,"It is not for the sun to catch up with the moon, nor for the night to outstrip the day. Each is floating in its own orbit"
  36,41,Another sign for them is that We carried their offspring in the loaded Ark
  36,42,and We created for them similar things on which they ride
  36,43,"If We willed, We could drown them, then there would be no one to respond to their cry, nor could they be rescued"
  36,44,"except by a mercy from Us, leaving them to enjoy for a while"
  36,45,"When it is said to them, “Beware of what is ahead of you and what is behind you, so that you may be shown mercy.”"
  36,46,No sign ever comes to them from their Lord except that they turn away from it
  36,47,"And when it is said to them, “Spend of what Allah has provided you with”, the disbelievers say to the believers, “Should we feed those whom Allah could feed if He willed? You are clearly misguided!”"
  36,48,"They say, “When will this promise come to pass, if you are truthful?”"
  36,49,They are not awaiting but a single Blast that will seize them while they are still disputing
  36,50,"Then they will not be able to make a will, nor will they be able to return to their households"
  36,51,"The Trumpet will be blown [again], and at once they will rush from their graves to their Lord"
  36,52,"They will say, “Woe to us! Who has resurrected us from our resting place?” [They will be told,] “This is what the Most Compassionate promised, and the messengers told the truth.”"
  36,53,"It will only be a single Blast, and at once they will all be brought before Us"
  36,54,"On that Day no soul will be wronged in the least, nor will you be recompensed except for what you used to do"
  36,55,"Indeed, on that Day the people of Paradise will be busy enjoying themselves"
  36,56,they and their spouses will be reclining on couches in the shade
  36,57,They will have therein fruits and all what they ask for
  36,58,"“Peace”: a word from a Most Merciful Lord"
  36,59,"“Stand apart [from the believers] this Day, O wicked ones"